  "short_text": "Even or Odd",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a line of space-separated integers and labels each integer as `Even` or `Odd`. The program should output each integer labeled accordingly.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input contains a single line of integers separated by space.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be a space-separated sequence of `Even` or `Odd` corresponding to each integer.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nIf the input is:\n\n```\n1 2 3 4\n```\n\nThe output should be:\n\n```\nOdd Even Odd Even\n```\n\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "b7b82b60-1bde-4340-a434-d9142ae54c61",
      "code_content": "def label_even_odd(numbers):\n    return [\"Even\" if num % 2 == 0 else \"Odd\" for num in numbers]\n\ninput_line = input().split()\nnumbers = [int(x) for x in input_line]\nlabels = label_even_odd(numbers)\nprint(\" \".join(labels))",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
